1400 ) and in Wales the chronicler  Geoffrey  of Monmouth (  d. 1155 ). The original form and meaning of the name is disputed. According to one theory, it is merely a variant of   Godfrey ;  others derive the first part from the Germanic word <i>gawia</i> ‘territory’, <i>walah</i> ‘stranger’, or <i>gisil</i> ‘pledge’. Medieval forms can be found to support all these theories, and it is possible that several names have fallen together, or that the name was subjected to reanalysis by folk etymology at an early date."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Mrs Geoffrey was born in 0957, in France. She had at least 1 son with Count of Brionne Geoffrey Count of Eu. She lived in Normandy, France in 957."},"et":{"0957–":"0957–Surnud","–Male":"Surnud","1000–1040":"1000–1040","0957–Female":"0957–Surnud","1000":"1000","1040":"1040","0957":"0957","about 1000":"umbes 1000","Brionne, Normandy, France":"Brionne, Eure, Normandie, Prantsusmaa","France":"Prantsusmaa","Normandy, France":"Normandie, Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"0957–":"0957–Kuollut","–Male":"Kuollut","1000–1040":"1000–1040","0957–Female":"0957–Kuollut","1000":"1000","1040":"1040","0957":"0957","about 1000":"noin 1000","Brionne, Normandy, France":"Brionne, Eure, Normandie, Ranska","France":"Ranska","Normandy, France":"Normandie, Ranska"},"fr":{"0957–":"0957–Décédée","–Male":"Décédé","1000–1040":"1000–1040","0957–Female":"0957–Décédée","1000":"1000","1040":"1040","0957":"0957","about 1000":"environ 1000","Brionne, Normandy, France":"Brionne, Eure, Normandie, France","France":"France","Normandy, France":"Normandie, France","lifeSummary":"Mrs Geoffrey est née en 0957, à France. Elle a eu au moins 1 fils avec Count of Brionne Geoffrey Count of Eu. Elle a vécu à Normandie, France en 957."},"de":{"0957–":"0957–Verstorben","–Male":"Verstorben","1000–1040":"1000–1040","0957–Female":"0957–Verstorben","1000":"1000","1040":"1040","0957":"0957","about 1000":"um 1000","Brionne, Normandy, France":"Brionne, Eure, Normandie, Frankreich","France":"Fr